title: Experimental Study of Excitation Functions and Isomer Ratios for Po-211,212.

x4freetext: EXPERIMENTAL STUDY OF EXCITATION FUNCTIONS AND
ISOMER RATIOS FOR PO-211,212.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.341, p.421 (1980)

x4freetext: THE ERRORS OF THE CROSS SECTIONS INCLUDE THE
STATISTICAL ERRORS OF THE EXPERIMENTAL COUNT RATES
AND SEVERAL SYSTEMATICAL UNCERTAINTIES. THE ERROR
OF THE CHARGE DUE TO INCOMPLETE CHARGE COLLECTION
IN THE FARADAY CUP WAS ASSUMED TO BE 5 PER CENT FOR
UNDEGRADED BEAMS AND 10 PER CENT FOR DEGRADED BEAMS.
THE TARGET THICKNESS HAS BEEN DETERMINED TO AN
ACCURACY OF 10 PER CENT. THE UNCERTAINTIES DUE TO THE
SOLID ANGLE AND THE FINITE BEAM SIZE MAY INTRODUCE
AN ERROR OF 4 PER CENT. THE USE OF THE
MULTISPECTRUMSCALING SYSTEM OF THE ANALYSER
INTRODUCED AN ERROR OF 5 PER CENT IN THE TIMING OF
THE SLOWPULSING EXREPIMENTS. THE RESULTING
SYSTIMATICAL ERRORS OF THE CROSS SECTIONS HAVE
VALUES ABOUT 20 PER CENT WHICH ARE IN MOST CASES
LARGER THAN THE STATISTICAL UNCERTAINTIES. THE
RELATIVE ERRORS OF THE ISOMER RATIOS ARE SMALLER THAN
THOSE OF THE CROSS SECTIONS IF THEY ARE EXTRACTED FROM
THE SAME EXPERIMENT. IN THIS CASE, ERRORS ASSOCIATED
WITH THE CHARGE, TARGET THICKNESS AND SOLID ANGLE
CANEEL.
METALLIC FOIL BI-209 (THICKNESS 0,6 G/CM-SQ).
